sentences: Webb moved to Nashville, Tennessee in 2011 after winning a songwriting competition in Greenville.
In 2012, Webb signed with Streamsound Records, a label founded by Byron Gallimore and Jim Wilkes.
He released his debut single, "It's All Good", in December 2012.
The song debuted at number 53 on the Billboard Country Airplay chart in February 2013.
Webb released his second single, "Slip On By", in July 2013 and it peaked on the Billboard Country Airplay chart at number 40 in early 2014.
